{{Infobox building |name = 595 Market Street |image = File:595 Market Street.jpg |location = 595 Market Street, [[San Francisco, California|San Francisco]], [[California]], [[United States]] |coordinates = {{Coord|37.789251|-122.400811|region:US-CA_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | pushpin_map = United States San Francisco Central#California#USA |roof = {{convert|410|ft|m|abbr=on}} |floor_count = 30 |floor_area = {{convert|429600|sqft|m2|abbr=on}}<ref name="tishman">{{cite web |url=http://www.tishmanspeyer.com/properties/595-market-street |title=595 Market Street |work=Tishman Speyer |accessdate=2013-02-27}}</ref> |building_type = Office |status = Completed |opening = 1979 |architect = [[Skidmore, Owings & Merrill]] |owner = [[Tishman Speyer]] }}
'''595 Market Street''' is a {{convert|410|ft|m|adj=on}} [[skyscraper]] at the corner of Second Street and [[Market Street (San Francisco)|Market Street]] in the [[Financial District, San Francisco|Financial District]] of [[San Francisco]], [[California]]. It contains 30 floors, and was completed in 1979. The [[hexagon]]al-shaped skyscraper was designed by [[Skidmore, Owings & Merrill]].
In 2009, [[Visa Inc.]] moved its corporate headquarters to 595 Market Street from [[San Mateo, California|San Mateo]], before deciding to move to [[Foster City, California|Foster City]] in October 2012.<ref>{{cite news |last=Leuty |first=Ron |url=http://www.bizjournals.com/sanfrancisco/news/2012/09/13/visa-headquarters-foster-city.html?page=all |title=Visa moving headquarters from San Francisco to Foster City |work=San Francisco Business Times |date=2012-09-13 |accessdate=2013-02-27}}</ref>
