{{Infobox officeholder |honorific-prefix = |honorific-suffix = <small>[[Order of Prince Henry|GOIH]] [[Order of Entrepreneurial Merit|GOMAIC]]</small> |image = |imagesize = 250px |office1 = [[Assembly of the Republic (Portugal)|Member of the Assembly of the Republic]] |term_start1 = 11 December 1995 |term_end1 = 23 October 1999 |constituency1 = [[Leiria District]] |birthname = Henrique José de Sousa Neto |birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1936|04|27}} |birth_place = [[Lisbon]], [[Estado Novo (Portugal)|Portugal]] |party = [[Socialist Party (Portugal)|Socialist Party]] <small>(1993-''present'')</small> |otherparty = [[Portuguese Communist Party]] <small>(1968-1975)</small> |spouse = |profession = [[Industrialist]] |children = 3 sons |alma_mater = |signature = |footnotes = }}
'''Henrique José de Sousa Neto''' (born 27 April 1936, in Lisbon) is a Portuguese [[entrepreneur]], [[industrialist]] and former member of the [[Assembly of the Republic (Portugal)|Portuguese parliament]] for the [[Socialist Party (Portugal)|Socialist Party]]. He founded the company [[Iberomoldes]] in 1975 and became one of the most noted businesspersons in the Portuguese engineering-related industry. Henrique Neto was the first candidate to step up for the [[Portuguese presidential election of 2016]].<ref>{{pt icon}} [http://www.jn.pt/PaginaInicial/Politica/Interior.aspx?content_id=4471266 Henrique Neto é o primeiro candidato oficial a Belém, Carla Soares, Jornal de Notícias, 23/03/2015]</ref>
==Early life== Born in [[Lisbon]] on April 27, 1936, Neto studied at first in the Lisbon Industrial School and then at the Commercial School of [[Marinha Grande]], a town from where his family had come from to Lisbon and where he moved at age 14. He began working as a metal worker apprentice in a mold factory, where he became director and later owner.<ref>{{pt icon}} [http://www.faz-acontecer.pt/autobiografia Autobiografia de Henrique Neto, Faz Acontecer]</ref>
==Career== In 1975 he founded [[Iberomoldes]], which would become in the following years the holding company of a group of twelve industrial companies and more than 1000 employees. It was from this group that SET was born, an engineering company especialized in innovative products development and IBEROLEFF in [[Pombal Municipality|Pombal]] for the production and export of components for automotive and industrial companies. He sold his position in 2009 to a co-founder.
Alongside its professional life in industry he also started very young in Portuguese politics and activism, influenced by his family environment which was not aligned with the [[Estado Novo (Portugal)|Estado Novo regime]]. He was affiliated with the MUD youth (an anti-regime organization), and participated in anti-regime conferences, illegally reproduced documents at home and worked actively in the presidential campaign of General [[Humberto Delgado]]. In 1969 he was even arrested for a while due to these anti-regime activities.
He joined the [[Portuguese Communist Party]] in 1968 but left it in 1975, after the [[Carnation Revolution]], in disagreement with the positions that were being taken, devoting himself thereafter only to business life. In 1993 Neto joined the [[Portuguese Socialist Party]] at the invitation of [[Jorge Sampaio]]. He was elected in 1995, and worked as a deputy until the end of his term as member of the Portuguese Parliament in 1999.<ref>{{pt icon}} [http://www.parlamento.pt/DeputadoGP/Paginas/Biografia.aspx?BID=1371 Biografia], Henrique José de Sousa Neto bio at the [[Portuguese Parliament]] webpage</ref>
