{{Main|Sectoral balances}}
'''Sectoral analysis''', also known as '''sectorial analysis''', is a [[statistic]]al [[analysis]] of the size, [[demographic]], pricing, competitive, and other economic dimensions of a sector of the [[economy]]. The analysis can be done by industry or by customer designation. The method was further developed by [[Wynne Godley]] for use in macroeconomic analysis of national economies.

