{{BLP IMDB refimprove|only=yes|date=October 2010}} {{Infobox person | name = Wallace Wolodarsky | image = | imagesize = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = | birth_place = [[United States]] | death_date = | death_place = | nationality = American | occupation = Screenwriter, actor, film director, producer | years_active = 1989-present | other_names = Wally Wolodarsky | spouse = [[Maya Forbes]] | children = | website = }}
'''Wallace Wolodarsky''', also billed as '''Wally Wolodarsky''', is an American actor, screenwriter, television producer and film director known for being one of the screenwriters for ''[[The Simpsons]]'' during the first four seasons with his writing partner [[Jay Kogen]].
==Career== As an actor, he has roles in ''[[Rushmore (film)|Rushmore]]'', ''[[The Darjeeling Limited]]'' and is a voice actor in ''[[Fantastic Mr. Fox (film)|Fantastic Mr. Fox]]'' and ''[[A Dog's Purpose (film)|A Dog's Purpose]]''.
==Personal life== His wife, Maya Forbes, is the sister of singer [[China Forbes]].<ref>[http://www.largeheartedboy.com/blog/archive/2010/06/maria_semple_in.html Maria Semple Interviews China Forbes of Pink Martini]</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Cornwell|first=Jane|title=The Pink Martini girl gets serious|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/music/3672840/The-Pink-Martini-girl-gets-serious.html|newspaper=Telegraph|date=24 Apr 2008}}</ref>
Wolodarsky is [[Jewish]].<ref>[http://www.csmonitor.com/2003/0912/p18s01-altv.html Fall TV preview] Goodale, Gloria. ''The Christian Science Monitor''. Published September 12, 2013. Accessed February 14, 2016.</ref>
